8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Jasper Art and Lexica share a solid foundation of core features including Text To Image, Commercial License. Where Jasper Art pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Style Transfer and Batch Generation, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Lexica uniquely offers Api Access, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Jasper Art holds an overall score of 5/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Lexica scores 6/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Lexica comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Jasper Art begins at $49/mo. Lexica stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Jasper Art requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
